  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="Aink290-kilavi">kāval mikutiyāṉ iravukkuṟi maṟukkappaṭṭu nīṅkiya talaimakaṉ vantuḻi 
          yavaṉ kēṭṭu veṟupput tīrttaṟ poruṭṭāl tiṉaippuṉaṅ kāval 
          toṭaṅkāniṉṟāḷ eṉpatu tōṉṟat tōḻi kūṟiyatu.
          
          </p>
        <p xml:lang="en"> 
          What the friend said, so that it might appear that [the heroine] had begun guarding the millet field, in order to remove the resentment of the hero who, having been refused the night-tryst due to excessive guarding, had gone away and then returned and asked.
          </p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="Aink290">
<l>aṟampuri ceṅkōṉ maṉṉaṉiṟ ṟānaṉi</l>
<l>ciṟantaṉa pōluṅ kiḷḷai piṟaṅkiya</l>
<l>pūkkamaḻ kūntaṟ koṭicci</l>
<l>nōkkavum paṭumava ḷōppavum paṭumē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>It seems that the parakeets are more excellent</l>
        <l>than the king with the straight sceptre who performs his duty.</l>
        <l>The creeper-like girl, whose tresses are fragrant with glossy flowers,</l>
        <l>happens to look at them, and happens also to drive them away.</l>
        
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
